[normal]UK Environmental Law Association – Supplementary written evidence[bold]Supplementary written evidence for the Joint Committee on the draft Deregulation Bill: clause 47(3)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Introductory comments[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Comments on [bold]Compatibility of [bold]Clause 47[bold](3) with the Aarhus Convention[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]PUBLIC PARTICIPATION DURING THE PREPARATION OF EXECUTIVE REGULATIONS AND/OR GENERALLY APPLICABLE LEGALLY BINDING NORMATIVE INSTRUMENTS
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]that
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Each Party shall strive to promote effective public participation at an appropriate stage, and while options are still open, during the 
[normal]preparation by public authorities of executive regulations and other generally applicable legally binding rules that may have a significant effect on the environment.  …
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]the repeal of this provision
[normal] would seem to represent a threat to compliance with the UK’s obligations under Aarhus.  
